Use the canonical `iii-architecture-diagram`, `iii-infographic`, `iii-slides`, and `iii-playground` skills from this repo. Cursor support is rules-based guidance, not native Agent Skills support.

When the user asks for:

- A diagram (SVG or PNG) of an iii deployment, worker, or dataflow → read `skills/iii-architecture-diagram/SKILL.md` and follow its workflow. Templates live in `skills/iii-architecture-diagram/templates/`.
- A system reference page, diff review, plan review, or project recap → read `skills/iii-infographic/SKILL.md`. Scaffold lives in `skills/iii-infographic/templates/index.html`; section snippets in `skills/iii-infographic/templates/section-snippets/`.
- A talk deck or presentation → read `skills/iii-slides/SKILL.md`. Scaffold lives in `skills/iii-slides/templates/deck.html`; slide snippets in `skills/iii-slides/templates/slide-snippets/`.
- A throwaway interactive editor (kanban triage, slider tuner, form editor with constraints, prompt split-preview, dataset curate) → read `skills/iii-playground/SKILL.md`. Scaffold lives in `skills/iii-playground/templates/playground.html`; pattern snippets in `skills/iii-playground/templates/playground-snippets/`. Primary export is `[copy as prompt]` for natural-language paste-back; `[copy as JSON]` is available as an optional second export when the agent expects structured input.

Each skill ships:
- `SKILL.md` — entrypoint, when-to-use, workflow.
- `references/*.md` — tokens, grammar, checklist, anti-patterns.
- `commands/*.md` — slash command templates (manual invocation in Cursor).
- `templates/*` — copy-paste starter scaffolds.

Generated diagrams and HTML pages should be written next to the source files unless the user specifies otherwise. Open in a browser if Cursor permits shell access; report the file path otherwise.
